Investor/VC Engagement Portal — Desktop Wireframes

Purpose
- Deliverable: Desktop wireframes that map UI to experiment treatments and explicit instrumentation hooks (data-event, component-id).
- Audience: Frontend dev (Kevin), PM, Experiment owners.

User flows covered
1. Discovery → Investor list → Investor profile → Start outreach
2. Deal discovery → Deal details → Save / Share / Request intro
3. Composer flow → Send outreach → Track opens/replies

Screen list & ASCII wireframes
1) Dashboard / Home
-------------------------------------------------------------
| Topbar: Logo | Search [search input] | UserMenu [avatar]   |
-------------------------------------------------------------
| Left Nav | Main: Insights cards (A/B variant tiles)           |
|         | - Quick filters (investor stage, sector)             |
|         | - Investor list (cards / table toggle)                |
-------------------------------------------------------------
| Footer                                                 [CTA] |
-------------------------------------------------------------

Notes:
- Search input: component-id="vc-search-input" data-event="search_submitted"
- Variant treatment: Experiment X toggles card density (A: compact list, B: expanded card)

2) Investor Card (list)
-------------------------------------------------------------
| [Logo] Investor Name (vc-investor-name)    [Follow CTA]     |
| Tags (sectors)                                    Last active |
| Short bio / notable investments                               |
-------------------------------------------------------------

Events:
- follow_click -> data-event="investor_followed" component-id="vc-investor-card-<id>"
- card_click -> data-event="investor_card_selected"

3) Investor Profile
-------------------------------------------------------------
| Header: investor name, follow, share (component-id="vc-investor-header") |
| Tabs: Overview | Deals | Network | Notes (tab_click -> data-event="profile_tab_selected") |
| Main: Deal list (each row has save, intro request, share buttons)          |
-------------------------------------------------------------

4) Outreach Composer Modal
-------------------------------------------------------------
| Modal (component-id="vc-composer-modal")                                |
| To: [investor chips] (emit: composer_recipient_added)                     |
| Subject: [input] (emit: composer_subject_focused)                         |
| Body: [rich editor] (emit: composer_body_edited - debounce 1s)            |
| Send CTA (data-event="outreach_sent")                                   |
-------------------------------------------------------------

Experiment Annotations (showing variant treatments)
- Experiment: CTA color test (A: Primary Blue #0A66FF, B: Primary Green #0FBF6A)
  - Components affected: follow CTA, send CTA
  - Indicate in wireframe with label: [Variant A/B]

Instrumentation guidance (desktop)
- Every actionable element must have:
  - component-id: kebab-case unique id (prefix vc-)
  - data-event attribute with event name
  - data-experiment attribute when variant-specific (e.g., data-experiment="cta_color_test:A")
- Use semantic HTML where possible (button, input, form). Emit events on user intent (click, submit, change).

Accessibility notes
- All icons have aria-labels
- Keyboard focus states required for CTAs and cards

Deliverable notes
- These wireframes are annotated and intended for implementation fidelity; see component_list.md and interaction_event_mapping.md for complete props and payloads.
